data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression tree construction is no longer needed. Replace with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type column naming changes (two issues)

- **Duplicate property names** (e.g. `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) now get uniquified with a numeric suffix — this generates a rename migration.
- **Nested complex types** now use the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` instead of the old `BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix:** pin column names explicitly to preserve existing schema:

```csharp
b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a =>
    a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a =>
    a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));

// Nested:
b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(x => x.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter. Add it:

```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
    DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)          // ← new parameter (redacted SQL)
{ /* logging — use logCommandText for safe log output */ }
```

Update all other methods on the interface similarly (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
